of this disease in a book full of intimate stories--including riveting courtroom testimony, secret investigations of women and doctors for abortion, and startling media portraits of children with disabilities. In exploring a disease that changed America, Dangerous Pregnancies powerfully illuminates social movements that still shape individual lives, pregnancy, medicine, law, and politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAbnormalities, HumanzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aAbortionzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aDisability awarenesszUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRubella in pregnancyzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aRubellazUnited StatesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a20th century american culture.  a20th century american medical history.  aabortion politics.  aabortion.  achildren with disabilities.  acourtroom testimony.  adangerous babies.  adisability rights movement.  adisability.  adisabled babies.  adisease.  adoctor.  adying babies.  afamily.  agerman measles epidemic.  agerman measles.  ahealth.  ainfant deaths.  amedicine.  amiscarriages.  amotherhood.  amothers.  anational anxiety.  anewborn babies.  aparenthood.  apregnancy.  apregnant women.  areproductive rights movement.  arubella.  ascience.  aserious birth defects.  asocial movements.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025903440uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094500540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520945005423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520945005/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY